summary: The winning ticket for the $800 million Mega Millions jackpot drawn on September 10, 2024, was purchased in Sugarland, Texas. A Florida ticket was also worth $1 million. The winning numbers were announced as: 2, 11, 22, 35, 62, with a Mega Ball of 23. The jackpot had been rolling over for 29 drawings since April 15, making it one of the largest prizes in Mega Millions history. The Texas winner has chosen to remain anonymous, while the Florida winner has not yet come forward.

name: Mexico
summary:
**Summary of News Article Titles:**

Mexico's judicial system faces significant changes under a sweeping overhaul proposed by the president, sparking controversy and protests. Protesters stormed the Senate to disrupt debates on the proposed constitutional amendment, while its passage has raised concerns about the health of Mexico's democracy. The U.S. Under-20 Women's National Team will face Mexico in the Round of 16 at the 2024 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup. Mexico's Senate approved changes to the constitution, with observers highlighting the significance of the move. The judicial reform proposal has cleared a commission stage and will proceed to a full Senate vote. The upcoming debate is described as a "make-or-break moment" for Mexico. Meanwhile, the article discusses the shifting dynamics of nearshoring in Mexico.

name: World Trade Center
summary: In the aftermath of the 9/11 attacks, Larry Silverstein, the developer behind the World Trade Center, faced an arduous task of rebuilding. Despite challenges and opposition, he persevered, outlasting several others involved in the project. The World Trade Center Health Program, which provides medical care to 9/11 first responders, is facing a funding shortage, with advocates calling for $3 billion in additional funding. The legacy of 9/11 continues to impact lives, with new cases of cancer and other health issues linked to the attack emerging. Artifacts from the World Trade Center serve as poignant reminders across Maine communities, while a survivor recounts their harrowing escape from the 81st floor of one of the towers. American Express is potentially set to anchor the development of Silverstein's 2 World Trade Center tower, while the number of FDNY members who have died from World Trade Center-related illnesses has surpassed those killed on 9/11, highlighting the ongoing toll of the tragedy.

name: Frankie Beverly and Maze
summary: Music legend Frankie Beverly, renowned for his soulful vocals and profound impact on the R&B and funk genres, has passed away at the age of 77. Beverly's exceptional talent propelled him to prominence as the co-founder and frontman of the influential band Maze. His timeless classics, such as "Before I Let Go," "Back in Stride," and "Can't Get Over You," have become enduring anthems that have inspired generations of music enthusiasts. Beverly's soulful delivery, coupled with the infectious grooves of Maze, captivated audiences and established him as a beloved figure in the music industry. News outlets across the country are mourning the loss of this musical icon, whose legacy will continue to resonate through his unforgettable melodies and heartfelt lyrics.

name: 2025 Social Security COLA increase
summary: Multiple news sources project a modest 2.5% cost-of-living adjustment (COLA) for Social Security benefits in 2025. This would represent the lowest increase since 2021 and a decrease from the 8.7% COLA implemented in 2023. Experts predict this decline due to a slowdown in inflation, which the COLA is calculated based on. While some retirees may experience a smaller increase in their benefits, some financial experts argue that this could be beneficial in the long run as it helps stabilize the Social Security program.
